Data delayed 15 minutes unless otherwise indicated.


















AboutMountain Province Diamonds is a Canadian diamond mining company
headquartered in Toronto, Ontario. In joint venture with De Beers, Mountain
Province operates the world's largest and richest new diamond mine—Gahcho Kué—located
in Canada's Northwest Territories.

MineGahcho Kué is the largest new diamond mine and
has the potential to become one of Canada's major high-grade and long-lived
diamond mines. The mine is on a 10,353 acre site located at Kennady Lake,
approximately 300 kilometres northeast of Yellowknife.
Learn MoreLeft: Gahcho Kué 67.87 carat gem quality diamondCompanyMountain Province Diamonds and De Beers Canada
are joint venture partners in the Gahcho Kué mine, which is the largest new diamond mine globally. Through its
joint venture with operating partner De Beers, the Company is well placed to
capitalize from the experience of the world's leading international diamond
producer.
Learn MoreInvestorsSee the current stock quotes and charts, our latest
corporate presentation, annual and quarterly financial reports, regulatory
filings, shareholder contacts and a list of analysts.
	
Investor InformationNewsMountain Province Diamonds strives to keep shareholders current through the issuance of regular news releases. View our latest news release and browse our archive of previous releases.
News ReleasesIndustryDiamond mines are extremely rare, and the world supply of
diamonds is expected to remain essentially flat over the next few decades as
demand increases. New supply is in high demand. Canada is the first country in
the developed world to produce and market high quality diamonds, and is
benefiting from an increasingly important role in the global market
