old short and not yet repurchased. Change from Last Percentage change in short interest from the previous report to the most recent report. Exchanges report short interest twice a month. Percent of Float Total short positions relative to the number of shares available to trade.      Short Interest (06/30/17)    Shares Sold Short 1.40 M     Change from Last  0.59%      Percent of Float 1.03%       ?    Money Flow Uptick/Downtick Ratio Money flow measures the relative buying and selling pressure on a stock, based on the value of trades made on an "uptick" in price and the value of trades made on a "downtick" in price. The up/down ratio is calculated by dividing the value of uptick trades by the value of downtick trades. Net money flow is the value of uptick trades minus the value of downtick trades. Our calculations are based on comprehensive, delayed quotes.      Stock Money Flow    Uptick/Downtick Trade Ratio  0 4    2.52      Net Money Flow ($)  56,115    Money flow gives a snapshot of relative buying and selling pressure in a stock. A ratio above one suggests greater buying pressure, below one suggests greater selling.               Advertisement         Competitors MPVD      Company Change P/E (TTM)    PGD Peregrine Diamonds Ltd.   -7.41% -0.01   -     CMP Compass Minerals International Inc.   +1.78% +1.20   17.34     SWY Stornoway Diamond Corp.   -1.19% -0.01   24.92     DDC Dominion Diamond Corp.   -0.14% -0.02   -        More information on MPVD   Competitor Data Provided By: capital cube           Profile MPVD      161 Bay Street Toronto Ontario M5J 2S1 Canada   Website Map       Employees  10    Sector  Gemstones      Sales or Revenue  -    Industry  Basic Materials/Resources      1Y Sales Change  -    Fiscal Year Ends December 31 Download Reports          David E. Whittle President, Chief Executive Officer & Director       Perry Y. Ing Chief Financial Officer       Patrick Charles Evans Director       Karen Goracke Director        More             Research 